  "poem_title": "Moomal Rano",
  "language": "Sindhi",
  "original_poem": "محبوب آيو جيءَ ۾،  \nساهه گهڙي ٿر ٿرن،  \nپڻين پارين جي،  \nلائي راڻو ڪن،  \nآسا مور مٿي سندر،  \nسُپڻي موئن،  \nمومل مور ٿيا،  \nڏيئي ڳڻين ڏيئي ڳڻين.\n\nريءَ ريءَ جوڳين،  \nجوڳين جيءُ سڙي سڙي،  \nپتڻ راڻا کڻي ڳرين،  \nجوڳين سڄڻ سندر ٿيا،  \nآسڻ ڳڻين آسڻ ڳڻين.",
  "translated_poem": "The beloved came into my soul,  \nBreath trembles in every moment,  \nI clutch the bangles on my wrists,  \nHolding Rano in my heart.  \nYearning above all, the mind in splendor,  \nIn dreams, I die for him,  \nMoomal waits, counting her sorrows,  \nCounting and counting her sorrows.\n\nFor the ascetics who tread this path,  \nTheir soul burns as they walk,  \nRano, take the ferry across,  \nThe ascetics have become one with their beloved,  \nCounting their hopes, counting their hopes.",
